<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[264,1324,1732,1878]" lastBlockId="14.[264,1326,284,1710]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="15" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis box="[264,615,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName box="[404,615,1732,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foveipygus">Hister foveipygus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is generally similar to the preceding species, and is only described here to the extent that they differ: Average length: 
<quantity box="[975,1065,1772,1798]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
(range 
<number box="[1154,1246,1772,1798]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.35" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.6</number>
); Avg. width: 
<quantity box="[349,442,1812,1838]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
(range 
<number box="[537,629,1812,1838]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="3.25" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.4</number>
); body smaller, more distinctly flattened, with the outline slightly but distinctly interrupted at the pronotal/elytral junction (
<figureCitation box="[1076,1152,1852,1878]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="12.[264,368,1211,1235]" captionTargetBox="[376,1211,566,1187]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[376,1211,566,1187]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dorsal habitus photographs of Hister spp. A. Hister guanacaste; B. H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169297/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1136,1152,1852,1878]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B); mandibles short, convex (rather than flattened) anteriorly; pronotal margin slightly more conspicuously convex; protibia narrower, with its apical tooth less prominent, its apical margin oblique (
<figureCitation box="[370,441,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[264,367,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[510,1087,776,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[499,1097,769,1813]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Posterior view of protibiae of Hister spp. A. Hister criticus; B. H. latimargo; C. H. guanacaste; D. H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158694/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[426,441,364,390]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
D); elytral stria 
<number box="[633,647,364,390]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="3.0">3</number>
more nearly and frequently complete (though still interrupted behind the middle in many individuals); striae 
<number box="[942,957,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
and 
<number box="[1026,1040,404,430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="5.0">5</number>
represented by deeply impressed apical fragments; propygidium with well defined, shallowly depressed, densely punctate area occupying most of its apical two­thirds, though with elevated impunctate margins on either side; pygidium similarly densely punctate in most of basal two­thirds, impunctate apically (
<figureCitation box="[511,582,564,590]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[264,367,1275,1299]" captionTargetBox="[364,1223,330,1248]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[364,1223,329,1249]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Photographs of propygidium and pygidium of Hister spp. A. Hister criticus; B. H. laevimargo; C. H. latimargo; D. H. guanacaste; E. H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/169296/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[566,582,564,590]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
E); all ventral tarsal setae fine, characteristically recurved back toward tarsus; male with tegmen of aedeagus smaller and more nearly parallel sided than above, its apical emargination very narrow, acute (
<figureCitation box="[872,945,644,670]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[264,368,1182,1206]" captionTargetBox="[450,1127,317,1146]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[450,1138,302,1163]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view of components of aedeagus of Hister spp. A. Tegmen of Hister criticus; B. Tegmen of H. guanacaste; C. Tegmen of H. foveipygus; D. Median lobe of H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[929,945,644,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
C); internal structure of median lobe and associated armature (
<figureCitation box="[618,687,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[264,368,1182,1206]" captionTargetBox="[450,1127,317,1146]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[450,1138,302,1163]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view of components of aedeagus of Hister spp. A. Tegmen of Hister criticus; B. Tegmen of H. guanacaste; C. Tegmen of H. foveipygus; D. Median lobe of H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[672,687,684,710]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
D) without obvious differences from that of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; female with valvifer of ovipositor relatively shorter than above, equal in length to coxite (
<figureCitation box="[354,427,764,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[264,368,1371,1395]" captionTargetBox="[635,943,731,1338]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[635,952,726,1347]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of valvifer and coxite (ovipositor) of Hister spp. A. Hister guanacaste; B. H. foveipygus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158697/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Fig. 
<number box="[412,427,764,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
B); six spermathecae present, four approximately equal in length to bursa, two about half as long. (Possible variation in number and degree of development of spermathecae has not been investigated. It seems unlikely that this difference from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be consistent.)
</paragraph>
